<p>The HP Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Block Storage Volume Operations uses the OpenStack Cinder
      service to manage storage volumes, including creating volumes, creating volume snapshots, and
      configuring volumes.</p>
<p>Once created, you can easily disconnect block storage volumes from one instance and attach them to another. You can also create snapshots of these volumes.</p>
<section id="working-with-the-volume-operations-service"> <title>Working with the Volume Operations Service</title>
<p>To perform tasks using the Volume Operations service, you can use the dashboard, API or CLI.</p>
</section>
<section id="UI"> <title>Using the dashboards</title>
<p>You can use the <xref
          href="../OperationsGuide/Dashboard/CGH-2-User-Dashboard-how-works.dita#topic6108c2udhw">HP
          Helion OpenStack Carrier Grade Dashboard</xref> to work with the Volume Operations
        service.</p>
</section>
<section id="API"> <title>Using the API</title>
<p>You can use a low-level, raw REST API for access to the Volume Operations service. See the <xref
          href="http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-blockstorage-v2.html" scope="external"
          format="html">OpenStack Block Storage API v2.0 Reference</xref>.</p>
</section>
<section id="cli"> <title>Using the CLI</title>
<p>You can use any of several command-line interfaces to access the Volume Operations service. See
          <xref href="http://docs.openstack.org/cli-reference/content/cinderclient_commands.html"
          scope="external" format="html">OpenStack Command Line Interface Reference</xref>.</p>
  <p>For more information on installing the command-line interface for interacting with services, see <xref href="http://docs.openstack.org/user-guide/content/install_clients.html" scope="external" format="html" >installing the OpenStack command-line clients</xref>.</p>
